  "interpretation": "The 10x10 genus-2 interference matrix measures how mod-ell fingerprint sharing between pairs of curves deviates from independence. Using 63255 genus-2 curves from LMFDB with Hecke traces at probes [41, 43], the raw interference matrix has SVD rank 6 (threshold sigma > sigma_max/100) and 99%-variance rank 4. The first 4 singular dimensions capture over 99% of the interference structure, indicating that mod-ell Galois representation correlations in genus-2 arithmetic are governed by ~4 independent dimensions.",
